g.text: Frittte clerk: "Mkay, here. I hope Saint-Batiste makes you feel better or something."
Frittte clerk: "Uhm... I don't know, let's see... Nosaphed is a nasal spray. Drouamine is a really good painkiller. Magnesium is a dietary supplement. Hypnogamma is..." She stops.
Frittte clerk: "Uhm..." She chews her bubblegum absent-mindedly. "No, sorry. I'm not, like, a doctor or anything."

Encyclopedia: She is right! Saint-Batiste the company derives its name from Saint-Batiste the city, itself so named... because that's what it is. A rare case where that really is the full etymological history -- as far as almost anyone knows, at least.
Frittte clerk: "Saint-Batiste? You know..." She nods slowly at the cabinet. "The pharmaceuticals company?"
Frittte clerk: Her nose is already back in her magazine. "Uh-huh."

Tutorial Agent: NOSAPHED heals +1 Health. DROUAMINE heals +3 Health. MAGNESIUM heals +1 Morale. HYPNOGAMMA heals +3 Morale.
Encyclopedia: Their logo is the bloodless rose -- pure white, untouched by harm.
Frittte clerk: "Yeah... there's like an ampoule somewhere." She waves her hand in the air absent-mindedly.
You: "Can you be a little more... specific?"
